  "body": "### Component\n\nForge\n\n### Have you ensured that all of these are up to date?\n\n- [X] Foundry\n- [X] Foundryup\n\n### What version of Foundry are you on?\n\nforge 0.1.0 (39b6e39 2022-03-08T00:04:30.511734+00:00)\n\n### What command(s) is the bug in?\n\nforge remappings\n\n### Operating System\n\nmacOS (amd)\n\n### Describe the bug\n\nWhen I type `forge remappings` I get this output\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge-std/=/Users/myworkspace/myproject/lib/forge-std/src/\r\nopenzeppelin-contracts/=/Users/myworkspace/myproject/lib/openzeppelin-contracts/contracts/\r\nds-test/=/Users/myworkspace/myproject/lib/ds-test/src/\r\n```\r\n\r\nI should instead get a **relative** path to the `lib/` folder, as reported in the [documentation](https://onbjerg.github.io/foundry-book/forge/dependencies.html#remapping-dependencies).\r\n\r\nExpected result:\r\n\r\n```\r\nforge-std/=lib/forge-std/src/\r\nopenzeppelin-contracts/=lib/openzeppelin-contracts/contracts/\r\nds-test/=lib/ds-test/src/\r\n```",
